{BEVERWIJK 1938  The steel industry commenced late in the Netherlands. Two
blast-furnaces were built in the dunes near Velsen after the First World War.
The company was called <->Hoogovens'. It had hobby clubs. The steel workers
began a chess club after Max Euwe became a world champion.   This small club
organised a New Year's tournament in 1938. Forty players took part in ten
groups during the weekend of 15 and 16 January. The first round was played on
Saturday evening. Sunday morning was devoted to churchgoing. Round two
occurred in the afternoon. Then a joint meal happened. Round three followed in
the evening and everybody went home thereafter.   Playing hall was the Casino,
canteen of the Hoogovens in Velsen.   Only locals participated. The crown
group was won by Philip Bakker and Jilling van Dijk (21/2/3).   One game has
survived. The chairman of the club encounters the great organiser of the event
in a minor group.} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 c6 5. Qc2 Nbd7 6. Bg5
